parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Loss of Brake Power with ABS Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of brake power can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on steep roads or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
zero resistance when pressing the brake pedal
ABS alarm sounds
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the brake pedal can cause driver distraction, loss of control, and increased stopping distance, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates when applied
especially at high speeds
and the vibration can occur at lower speeds over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front differential ring gear can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, leading to safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: Ring gear failure
ring gear failure with damage to the housing
repeated failure of the front differential.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the transmission is overridden
the vehicle bucks forward
the vehicle does not respond to gear changes
the vehicle only stops when the ignition is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the sunroof can cause shock, distraction, and potentially lead to loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Loud explosion sound
sudden shattering of the sunroof
hole in the sunroof
debris falling into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Anti-Theft Chip Failure in Remote Key
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft chip in the remote key can cause inconvenience, frustration, and financial loss due to the need to replace the entire computer unit.
symptoms: Remote key no longer functions
anti-theft chip falls out
unable to start or unlock the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt latch can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to rear seat occupants.
symptoms: The rear seat belt buckle does not latch properly
the rear seat belt comes undone while driving
the rear seat belt is difficult to fasten
the rear seat belt is difficult to unfasten.
